Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the South Court Auditorium in the Eisenhower Executive Office Building to celebrate Black History Month. She thanked Majority Leader Steny Hoyer for his leadership and acknowledged the political, business, and community leaders in attendance. Harris discussed the importance of truth-telling and addressing the challenges faced by black Americans during the COVID-19 pandemic. She highlighted the American Rescue Plan, which includes funding for vaccinations, financial support for individuals and families, and assistance for small businesses. Harris emphasized the need for equity in distributing resources and acknowledged the contributions of black scientists and healthcare workers. She urged everyone to continue the relay race of history, working towards justice and equality. Harris concluded by quoting Coretta Scott King and encouraging perseverance and determination in the face of challenges.